        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2/numerical-code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria — MRL 5",
        "description": "Solver must demonstrate observed order of accuracy within 10% of theoretical order on at least three manufactured-solution benchmarks relevant to rotating machinery flows (Taylor-Couette, lid-driven cavity, rotating disk). Code verification report must be peer-reviewed or published."
      },
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification against three ASME V&V 20 manufactured-solution benchmarks confirmed second-order spatial accuracy (observed p=1.94 vs. theoretical p=2.0) and first-order temporal accuracy for unsteady cases. Published verification report (Stewart et al., J. Fluids Eng. 2022) accepted as peer-reviewed evidence."
    },
