        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — GCI < 2%",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) must be below 2% for the hemolysis index QoI on a three-level structured mesh refinement study. y+ ≤ 1 on all wetted surfaces. Temporal discretization error must be demonstrated to be negligible relative to spatial GCI via time-step refinement study."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (4.1M, 11.2M, 28.7M cells) yielded GCI=1.3% for the normalized hemolysis index at the nominal operating point (Q=5 L/min, 2800 RPM). Maximum y+=0.87 across all wetted surfaces. Time-step halving study confirmed temporal error <0.4% of spatial GCI. Production mesh: 11.2M cells."
    },
    {
