        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — experimental fidelity",
        "description": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within stated measurement uncertainties. Blood analogue fluid properties (viscosity, density) must be characterized at test temperature. Flow rate and rotational speed must be controlled to within ±2% of nominal. Hemolysis measurement protocol must follow ASTM F1841 or equivalent."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental campaign conducted with porcine blood at 37±0.5 °C, haematocrit 40±2%. Flow rate controlled to ±0.8% via Coriolis meter; rotor speed controlled to ±5 RPM. Hemolysis measured per modified ASTM F1841 protocol with plasma-free haemoglobin quantified by spectrophotometry. All five operating points within the declared operating envelope."
    },
    {
