        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — absolute hemolysis index",
        "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands (U95) at all five operating points. Systematic bias must be less than 15% of mean experimental NIH. Scatter metric (RMSE/mean) must be below 0.20."
      },
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values at all five operating points fell within U95 uncertainty bands of experimental measurements. Mean absolute error = 8.3% of experimental mean NIH. RMSE/mean = 0.11. No systematic bias detected (Wilcoxon signed-rank test, p=0.41). Exceeds acceptance criteria; achievedLevel elevated to 5."
    },
    {
