        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump) as the COU device model. Operating conditions in validation experiments must overlap with the COU operating envelope. Blood analogue or actual blood must be used (water-glycerol surrogates are insufficient at MRL 5)."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (identical CAD to simulation geometry). All five validation operating points are within the COU operating envelope. Porcine blood was used (not water-glycerol surrogate), satisfying the MRL 5 requirement for physiological fluid fidelity. Geometry and boundary condition mapping documented in validation plan VP-COU2-2024."
    },
