        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria — iterative convergence",
        "description": "Residuals must converge to below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity and momentum equations. Force and moment monitors on impeller must achieve cycle-to-cycle variation below 0.5%. Solver round-off error must be assessed via double-precision comparison."
      },
      "rationale": "All residuals converged to ≤1×10⁻⁶ within 2500 iterations per operating point. Impeller torque monitor showed cycle-to-cycle variation of 0.12%. Double-precision vs. single-precision comparison showed negligible difference (<0.01% in NIH). Achieves level 4, exceeding the MRL 5 required level of 3."
    },
    {
