        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — turbulence and hemolysis sub-models",
        "description": "Turbulence model selection must be justified by comparison of at least two turbulence closure models against experimental velocity data. Hemolysis sub-model (power-law or equivalent) must be calibrated against independent hemolysis data not used in the primary validation. Model form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the total UQ budget."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected after comparison with k-ε realizable and RSM closures against PIV velocity measurements (SST k-ω showed lowest RMS error of 4.2% vs. 7.8% and 9.1%). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model calibrated against Arora et al. (2004) independent dataset. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% of NIH (90% CI) and included in Monte Carlo UQ budget."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
