        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — blood rheology and geometry",
        "description": "Blood viscosity and density must be characterized from the same blood lot used in experiments, with measurement uncertainty reported. Pump geometry must be verified against as-built CMM measurements with dimensional deviations documented. Inlet velocity profile must be specified from upstream flow conditioning measurements."
      },
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (3.5±0.2 mPa·s) and density (1055±3 kg/m³) measured from experimental blood lot using cone-plate rheometer and pycnometer. CMM inspection of FDA pump confirmed maximum dimensional deviation of 0.03 mm from nominal CAD (within ±0.05 mm envelope). Inlet velocity profile extracted from LDV measurements 2D upstream of pump inlet."
    },
    {
