      },
      "rationale": "Hemolysis experiments conducted with porcine blood from four independent donors (n=4 per operating point, 20 total experiments). Inter-donor CV ranged from 8–14% across operating points, consistent with published literature. One outlier identified (donor 3, Q=3 L/min) and excluded per pre-specified Grubbs test criterion (p<0.05); documented in experimental report EXP-COU2-2024."
    },
